## Task: Implement system theme preference detection

**Branch:** `task/68-109-mvp-sync-verso-removal` (already checked out)
**PR:** #117
**Issues:** #68, #109

### What to do

**File 1: `/Users/eric/GitHub/Side-By-Side-Blueprint/toolchain/dress-blueprint-action/assets/plastex.js`**

Read the file first. The current `getPreferredTheme()` function (around lines 3-11) always defaults to 'light' when no localStorage preference exists. It looks like:
```javascript
function getPreferredTheme() {
  const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('sbs-theme');
  if (savedTheme) {
    return savedTheme;
  }
  return 'light';
}
```

Change it to check system preference as fallback:
```javascript
function getPreferredTheme() {
  const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('sbs-theme');
  if (savedTheme) {
    return savedTheme;
  }
  if (window.matchMedia && window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches) {
    return 'dark';
  }
  return 'light';
}
```

Also find the comment about system preference listener being disabled (around lines 33-34) and replace it with an active listener:
```javascript
// Listen for system theme changes (only applies when no saved preference)
if (window.matchMedia) {
  window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').addEventListener('change', function(e) {
    if (!localStorage.getItem('sbs-theme')) {
      applyTheme(e.matches ? 'dark' : 'light');
    }
  });
}
```

**File 2: `/Users/eric/GitHub/Side-By-Side-Blueprint/toolchain/dress-blueprint-action/assets/common.css`**

Read the file. Find the `html[data-theme="dark"]` block (around line 250). After the existing dark mode block ends, add a CSS-only fallback for the brief moment before JS runs:

```css
/* System preference fallback -- applies before JS sets data-theme attribute */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  html:not([data-theme]) {
    --sbs-bg-page: #252525;
    --sbs-bg-surface: #1a1a1a;
    --sbs-bg-card: #2d2d2d;
    --sbs-text: #f0f0f0;
    --sbs-text-muted: #cccccc;
    --sbs-border: #cccccc;
    --sbs-link: #60a5fa;
    --sbs-link-hover: #93c5fd;
  }
}
```

Copy the most critical variables from the `html[data-theme="dark"]` block. Don't duplicate all of them -- just the ones that would cause visible flash (backgrounds, text, links, borders). This prevents FOUC (flash of unstyled content) on dark-mode systems.

